larch-unpublished-api-checker 1.0.1 addressing the issue from 1.0.0.\n\nThe upgrade process involves updating the dependency management section in pom.xml...\n\nContinuing through the standard plugin changes, I see the UI development template is updating RequireJS from 2.1.11 to 2.3.7, and the UI build tool is also being updated to align with the RequireJS version upgrade. The source document emphasizes that when upgrading, users need to review all release notes between their current version and 5u26 to understand the cumulative changes. While the knowledge file focuses on 5u26-specific updates, the historical context from earlier versions matters for migration planning—though that information would typically live in those respective release notes rather than here.\n\nLooking at the actual sheet structure, it contains all historical changes accumulated, but the knowledge file has reasonably filtered to just the 5u26 entries since this is the 5u26 release note. The section header does specify \"5u26での変更点\" to clarify the scope.\n\nLet me verify the omissions more systematically by checking each entry against what's captured.\n\nFor No.2 on route reload, the source specifies this applies to blank project templates, and the knowledge file correctly identifies the specific file path for container web applications. The change type is marked as \"変更\" in the source, and the knowledge file captures this accurately.\n\nNow I'm checking the standard plugin changes sheet - the knowledge file only documents the 5u26 entries, but there's additional content in the source that appears to be cut off mid-sentence about version update procedures. 標準プラグインの変更点を確認する際、5u26固有の変更内容がナレッジファイルに含まれているのに対して、過去のバージョン（1.4.2から5u19まで）の履歴データは含まれていないことに気づいた。これはリリースノート文書の性質上、各バージョンの変更内容は対応するリリースノートに記載されるべきもので、5u26への更新ガイドとしては現在のバージョン情報で十分だと判断できる。\n\n検証を進めると、JSON値の区切り文字に関する説明と、env.propertiesのnablarch.routesMapping.checkIntervalプロパティのデフォルト値の修正内容が、ナレッジファイルの記述と一致していることが確認できた。\n\nその後、コンテナ用アプリケーションのプロファイル設定