ion names, Property names, and XxxException names—these Maven artifact IDs don't strictly fit those categories. I'm scanning through the content sections for actual class names and annotations, but I'm not finding specific PascalCase classes or @Annotation names that should be included in the hints.\n\nI did spot one property name that matches the criteria: `nablarch.routesMapping.checkInterval`. As for the JIRA issue numbers, those aren't typically part of hint validation.\n\nLooking at my findings, there's a critical issue where `official_doc_urls` references a URL that doesn't actually appear in the source file. There are also minor gaps—`nablarch-single-module-archetype` and `nablarch-plugin-bundle` appear in the source but aren't captured in the hints, though these are borderline cases since they're module names rather than the specific categories being checked.\n\nRegarding the historical plugin data spanning multiple versions—I realize this is intentional scoping since the knowledge file is specifically for 5u26 changes, and the note about checking all versions when upgrading is already included. That's not an omission worth flagging.\n\nNow I'm finalizing my assessment. I've identified one critical fabrication in the `official_doc_urls` field that has no source basis, plus two minor gaps where the hints are missing references to `nablarch-single-module-archetype` and `nablarch-plugin-bundle` despite these modules being mentioned in the content. I'll format these findings as JSON.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":30219,"cache_read_input_tokens":18400,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":30219,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ead5b59-c7ab-4f30-8af7-81210939a593","uuid":"e6fec564-2d49-4850-aca5-795fd32caca9"}
